caption: Honestly, I’ve tried a lot of different gyro carts most  of them are ok: tasty, cheap and fills you up, but this place is something special. This cart serves the best and I mean the best Gyro in Brooklyn and most likely in New York City. I promise you that if you’re going to be craving mix over rice or a gyro sandwich you will come to this place with no hesitation. This is the place that has a line of people everyday at anytime of day or night. 10 out of 5 !!!

Absolutely delicious. I got a falafel sandwich that tasted like home. The lines get long, but move along quickly, make sure an order two so you don't have to get back in line like me. Price is very reasonable. Flavors are so true to real middle Eastern falafel, that's exactly how it should taste. Next trip to New York is with out a doubt going to include a stop here again. Basically if you want a authentic flavorful sandwich this is the place to get it.

This is still the classic place for late night greasy, satisfying “halal” grub in Bay Ridge. Still haven’t tried that other dude’s cart across the street and probably never will. Recommended.

Without a doubt the most recognizable halal cart in South Brooklyn. If you're in Bay Ridge this is the spot that everyone hits up after a night of drinking, or late commute home from work. The food is incredible in terms of flavor and portions. It's cheap and delicious. They hook everyone up with even the smallest of requests. Everyone who works in that cart is a hustler and has a great attitude. You can go there at 3 am in the dead of winter and still wait on a line to get an order in, that's how popular this spot is.

The absolute best!! Delicious gyros. After the subway lets out there will be a bit of a line, but they quietly and confidently keep it moving. The hot sauce is crazy spicy, and they don't always have little cups to allow for taking it on the side, but that's a small quibble.

I was in the Bay Ridge area for a couple days arrived from Chicago and wanted to try a mixed plate from one of the food carts in the area, a friend of mine recommended I go to the Middle Eastern Halal food cart next to Citi Bank. I ordered the mixed chicken over rice with lamb and it was the best mixed chicken over rice middle eastern halal food I’ve had, very clean professional and friendly. The food is very tasty and perfectly prepared and seasoned, the employees are very respectful. I really recommend this specific food cart to everyone who loves tasty food and enjoys the flavor of perfectly spiced chicken and rice, I wish that one day they will open one in Chicago.
